---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Boards & Colors | TimberTech Composite Decking Tiers | Belvedere Decks"
  description="The three decking tiers we install, in plain English: TimberTech Prime+ (our recommendation for most decks), TimberTech PRO, and Advanced PVC. Real colors, real trade-offs, no catalog overwhelm."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Boards &amp; Colors</p>
      <h1>Three tiers. A few great colors. No catalog overwhelm.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        TimberTech makes dozens of boards. You don't need to compare dozens of boards.
        These are the three tiers we actually install, why each exists, and the colors
        we recommend most. Every tier sits on the same code-perfect structure — we never
        tier the safety.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Good · Our recommendation for most decks</p>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">TimberTech Prime+</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        This is the board we install more than any other. Capped composite with the
        wood look, none of the staining and sealing, and a 25-year fade and stain
        warranty — at the price point that makes most resurfacing budgets work.
      </p>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 28px;">
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/edge-prime-dark-cocoa.jpg" alt="Outdoor furniture on a TimberTech Prime+ composite deck in Dark Cocoa" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Dark Cocoa — the rich brown most people picture when they say "new deck." <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/edge-sea-salt-gray.jpg" alt="TimberTech Prime+ composite deck in Sea Salt Gray" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Sea Salt Gray — the light, coastal gray that hides pollen and paw prints. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/edge-coconut-husk-picture-frame-1.jpg" alt="Two-tone TimberTech deck in Coconut Husk with a Sea Salt Gray picture-frame border" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Coconut Husk with a Sea Salt Gray border — the two-tone picture frame we build standard. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Better</p>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">TimberTech PRO — Reserve Collection</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        A step up in grain realism and scratch resistance, with a 30-year fade and
        stain warranty. Worth it on high-traffic decks, pool surrounds, and anywhere
        dogs and furniture slide around.
      </p>
      <div class="grid cols-2" style="margin-top: 28px; align-items: start;">
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/reserve-antique-leather-pool.jpg" alt="Poolside TimberTech Reserve composite deck in Antique Leather with lounge chairs" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Antique Leather beside a pool — PRO boards shrug off wet traffic. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div>
          <h3>When we steer you here</h3>
          <p>
            If your deck is the main path to a pool or hot tub, hosts big gatherings, or
            you simply want deeper, hand-scraped grain underfoot, PRO is the honest
            middle answer: noticeably nicer than Prime+, meaningfully cheaper than PVC.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Best</p>
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">TimberTech Advanced PVC</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        No wood fibers at all, which means the lightest colors stay cool and clean, the
        boards weigh less on your frame, and the warranty runs up to 50 years. This is
        the architectural grade — the board for the deck you never want to think about again.
      </p>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 28px;">
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/apvc-french-white-oak.jpg" alt="TimberTech Advanced PVC deck in French White Oak, Landmark Collection" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>French White Oak — the bright, Scandinavian look only PVC can hold. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/apvc-mahogany-vintage.jpg" alt="TimberTech Vintage Collection PVC decking in Mahogany on a premium deck" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>Mahogany, Vintage Collection — the deep, furniture-grade tone. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="site-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/apvc-castlegate-overhead.jpg" alt="Overhead close-up of TimberTech CastleGate Landmark Collection deck boards" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption>CastleGate up close — this is the grain realism you're paying for. <span class="photo-credit">Photo courtesy of TimberTech</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid cols-2" style="align-items: center;">
        <div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Built from recycled material, made in the USA</h2>
          <p>
            TimberTech composite boards are made with up to about 80% recycled wood and
            plastic, manufactured in the USA. Your old deck's replacement keeps material
            out of the landfill — and never asks for stain again.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
            We also install Trex. If you have your heart set on it, say so at the visit
            and we'll price it alongside these tiers.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="site-figure badge-figure">
          <img src="/images/timbertech/badge-recycled-material.png" alt="TimberTech recycled material, made in the USA badge" loading="lazy" style="max-width: 180px;" />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">See the real colors on your actual deck.</h2>
      <p>
        Photos get you close; samples in your backyard light settle it. Every estimate
        visit brings boards you can hold, and your exact price in all three tiers —
        same visit.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 0;"><a class="btn primary" href="/estimate">Get a Free Estimate</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
